-- Calpers Commodity Holdings Climbed 0.4% in March to $1.284B
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2013-05-14T21:25:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-14/calpers-commodity-holdings-climbed-0-4-in-march-to-1-284b.html
The California Public Employees’
Retirement System, the largest U.S. pension fund, reported the
value of its commodity holdings rose 0.4 percent in March from
the previous month.  The fund held $1.284 billion in commodities as of March 31,
the most-recent data available, or 0.5 percent of the total
assets listed at $257.395 billion, according to a monthly  report 
posted on the fund’s website for yesterday’s investment
committee  meeting . That’s up from $1.279 billion on  Feb. 28 , or
0.5 percent of total assets of $254.997 billion.  The fund’s board met yesterday and today and will meet
tomorrow, according to the Calpers  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in Chicago at 
